import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['budgetYear', 'value']]
    data = data.groupby('budgetYear').mean().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data['budgetYear'], data['value'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['value'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Budget Allocation')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of budget allocation over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['value'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.75)
    plt.axvline(data['value'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['value'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Value')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecast values?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['budgetYear', 'forecastYear', 'value']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['budgetYear'], data['value'], label='Budget', alpha=0.5)
    ax.scatter(data['forecastYear'], data['value'], label='Forecast', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Value')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between budget and forecast values?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = data['budgetYear'].astype(int)
    data['value'] = data['value'].astype(float)
    avg_budget = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_budget['budgetYear'], avg_budget['value'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=avg_budget['value'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average')
    ax.set_xlabel('Budget Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Budget Allocation')
    ax.set_title('What is the average budget allocation per year?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['abs_diff'] = np.abs(data['value'])
    grouped_data = data.groupby('forecastYear').mean().reset_index()
    plt.plot(grouped_data['forecastYear'], grouped_data['abs_diff'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=grouped_data['abs_diff'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Absolute Difference')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
